Solution to find employees who have the highest salary in each of the departments.

---------------------------------------------------------------

WITH DEPT_HIGHES_SAL AS
(
  SELECT DEPARTMENTID, MAX(SALARY) AS HIGHEST_SAL
  FROM EMPLOYEE
  GROUP BY DEPARTMENTID
)


SELECT DPT.NAME AS DEPARTMENT, EMP.NAME AS EMPLOYEE, H_SAL.SALARY AS HIGHEST SALARY
FROM DEPT_HIGHEST_SAL H_SAL
INNER JOIN EMPLOYEE EMP
ON H_SAL.HIGHEST_SAL = EMP.SALARY 
AND H_SAL.DEPARTMENTID = EMP.DEPARTMENTID
INNER JOIN DEPARTMENT DPT 
ON DPT.ID = H_SAL.ID


This is great performance and readability-wise, but if I need to find the nth highest and the 2nd highest, then I can't
Implement the same logic, and if I need to modify this logic, it becomes very expensive. 

using window function this could be handled - 


  WITH DEPT_HIGHEST_SAL AS
(SELECT DEPARTMENTID,NAME, SALARY, DENSE_RANK() OVER 
(PARTITION BY DEPARTMENTID ORDER BY SALARY DESC) AS RNK 
FROM EMPLOYEE)

SELECT DPT.NAME AS DEPARTMENT, H_SAL.NAME AS EMPLOYEE, H_SAL.SALARY
FROM DEPT_HIGHEST_SAL H_SAL 
INNER JOIN DEPARTMENT DPT 
ON H_SAL.DEPARTMENTID= DPT.ID
WHERE H_SAL.RNK=1  


THIS window function could be modified to get any nth highest or lowest salary 

